An Act requiring licensed gun owners to submit a yearly affidavit.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 129B of chapter 140 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended in paragraph 8 by inserting after the word “information”, in
3 line 259, the following words: – or who fails to annually notify the licensing authority pursuant
4 to paragraph (11A).
5 SECTION 2. Said section 129B, as so appearing, is hereby further amended by inserting
6 after paragraph 10 the following paragraph:–
7 (11A) Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (9), a cardholder shall annually verify
8 by written notice, in the form of a sworn affidavit or declaration to the licensing authority that
9 issued such card, that the cardholder has not lost a firearm or had a firearm stolen from the
10 cardholder's possession since the date of the cardholder's last renewal or issuance.
